.TH tpm2_createpolicy 8 "February 2017" Intel "tpm2.0-tools"
.SH NAME
tpm2_createpolicy\ - Creates simple assertion authorization policies. Support in this tool version is for policy based on pcr
and single pcr index only.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tpm2_createpolicy[ COMMON OPTIONS ] [ TCTI OPTIONS ] [ \fB\-\-policyfile\fR|\fB\-\-policyPCR\fR|\fB]
.PP
Creates simple assertion authorization policies. Support in this tool version is for policy based on pcr 
and a single pcr index only.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tpm2_createpolicy
Creates simple assertion authorization policies. Support in this tool version is for policy based on pcr 
and a single pcr index only. It can then be used with object creation and or tools using the object.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-P ,\-\-policyfile\fR
File to save the created policy digest (string,  required, default:NULL). 
.TP
\fB\-I ,\-\-policyPCR\fR
Identifies the policy type as policyPCR & takes a single pcr index input to create the policy of policyPCR type (string, required, default:NULL). 
@COMMON_OPTIONS_INCLUDE@
@TCTI_OPTIONS_INCLUDE@
.SH ENVIRONMENT\@TCTI_ENVIRONMENT_INCLUDE@
.SH EXAMPLES
.B tpm2_createpolicy
.PP
.nf
.RS
Create a authorization policy tied to a specific PCR index: 
tpm2_createpolicy --policyPCR < # between 0 and 24 > --policyfile < "file.name" >
tpm2_createpolicy -I 0 -P policy.file
.RE
.fi
